text: Harriet M. Hageman (born October 18, 1962) is an American lawyer and Republican politician. She is the member of the U.S. House of Representatives representing Wyoming's at-large congressional district since 2023. In August 2022, Hageman beat incumbent U.S. Representative Liz Cheney in a landslide victory. Her campaign was supported by former President Donald Trump. She was a candidate for Governor of Wyoming in the 2018 election. ==References== Category:1962 births Category:Living people Category:Lawyers from Wyoming Category:United States representatives from Wyoming Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
